message.content: cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.ET - The paper discusses brain-inspired and fault-tolerant foundational innovations to the system architecture of massively parallel tiled computer architectures and the corresponding programming paradigm. It also mentions the development of a dedicated cortical simulation benchmark. These topics are related to the fields of artificial intelligence, neural networks, parallel computing, and embedded systems, which are covered by the above-mentioned sub-categories.
